<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-15677] Topology events are not sent to clients if the nodes use the same network interface</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15677</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;This bug only happens when the cassandra nodes are configured to use a single network interface (ip) but different ports.&#160; See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7544&quot; title=&quot;Allow storage port to be configurable per node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7544&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7544&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue: The topology events aren&apos;t sent to clients. The problem is that the port is not taken into account when determining if we send it or not:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/transport/Server.java#L624&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/transport/Server.java#L624&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# I think the cassandra-test branch is required to get the -S option (USE_SINGLE_INTERFACE)
ccm create -n4 local40 -v 4.0-alpha2 -S
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Then run this small python driver script:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; time
from cassandra.cluster &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; Cluster

cluster = Cluster()
session = cluster.connect()

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; True:
    print(cluster.metadata.all_hosts())
    print([h.is_up &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; h in cluster.metadata.all_hosts()])
    time.sleep(5)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then decommission a node:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ccm node2 nodetool disablebinary
ccm node2 nodetool decommission
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
You should see that the node is never removed from the client cluster metadata and the reconnector started.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
